Osage Education Foundation
September 8 at 10:07 PM ¬∑

Patience, compassion, and understanding are three attributes our 2020 Distinguished Alumni have shown prior to Covid-19, and even more during this pandemic with our ever moving event date. At our September board meeting, we decided to postpone the 2020 Distinguished Alumni event to Homecoming weekend in 2021. We will let you know the exact date, when the 2021 school activities calander is approved. In the mean time, we can‚Äôt thank our wonderful 2020 Distinguished Alumni winners for being so understanding!

Pat Mackin, class of 1966

Emily Schmidt Massey, class of 1992

Joyce Larson Ruehlow, class of 1979

Bruce Olson, class of 1973

We now have an extra year to recognize how truly great you all are!

shared_text:
Mrs. Huftalin's 3rd grade
September 1 at 6:12 PM ¬∑

Over the last 3 days, in 3rd grade science we have been learning about what it takes to be a great "teammate" or "engineering team". After logging into Schoology and watching a video of Mrs. Huftalin explain the project the teams were faced with the problem of saving Fred the Worm who lost his life vest while whitewater rafting. The students worked really hard together to come up with a plan, test the plan, and then make any improvements and test it again. They could only touch the 2 paperclips provided and not Fred, the life vest, or the raft!! Today we ended with each team sharing out. We also enjoyed eating some extra worms!

What an amazing start to the school year!!! We can't say enough positive things about the students, staff, and community as we started the 2020-2021 school year! It feels so good having school back in session and there has been so much kindness and cooperation as students and staff worked together with community and family support! Way to go GREEN DEVIL NATION!!! SO PROUD of YOU!!
Tomorrow we venture into true on-line learning as we begin with our first Wednesday of planned on-line learning and our first day for our families who are learning virtually every day! THANK YOU to all for making this possible and remember TOGETHER, we can virtually do anything!!!!

post_text:
We are SO EXCITED to see our students tomorrow!!! We know there are lots of changes and we will all need to be kind, caring, and patient with each other. Please ask us questions and be positive around your children! Yes, it is going to be warm this week (thanks mother nature) and we will be taking lots of breaks as we get back into a routine for the first time in 5 1/2 months.
Below you see our theme for the year for our staff this year! We have an awesome staff who works TOGETHER and they can do anything we put our minds to! See you in the morning GREEN DEVILS! We are so excited to see you!!!!

Mrs. Ryan's 4th Grade Osage Class
August 22 at 5:30 PM ¬∑

Student and staff safety is at the forefront of EVERY decision made.

The Osage School District understands the inconvenience that the decision to not offer in-town bussing will cause families.

In order to balance safety and our strong desire to still offer face-to-face learning, difficult decisions have had to be made regarding transportation in order to serve the ones most in need of bussing.

A great deal of time and efforts have been put towards creating walking school busses and to increase the safety of children needing to cross busy roads.

FAMILIES: Please have your children utilize new crossing guard locations, whether they are walking or riding a bike. These locations are: 5th and Main (Hwy 9), 7th and Mechanic (Hwy 218), and 7th and Vine.
#weareosage

shared_text:
Connie Ainsworth Ryan
August 18 at 7:43 PM ¬∑

#WeAreOsage

If you have a child, grandchild, or neighbor attending the Osage School District, I pray that you find comfort in the extraordinary efforts that the school & community organizations have taken in preparing for this fall and the children receiving the safest & best possible education, considering the current situation. A countless amount of hours of discussions have taken place, most teachers attended webinars, digital conferences, and participated in many Zoom meetings.

It‚Äôs IMPOSSIBLE to describe the shear admiration, satisfaction, and pride I have towards the Osage School District, the administration, the teachers, paras, custodians, drivers, cooks, media specialists, instructional coaches, health office, and secretaries. I am proud to work with such dedicated staff & even more excited to work back with the children, in whatever form is allowed.

Together, we can VIRTUALLY do ANYTHING!!
